---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Pagination from '../../../components/Pagination.astro';
const base = '/portfolio';
const previous = null;
const next = 'elevator';
---
<BaseLayout title="Expression Evaluator | ADEN Project" base={base}>
  <Pagination base={base} section="projects/aden" previous={previous} next={next} />
  <h1>Expression Evaluator</h1>

  <section style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <p>
      A parser and evaluator that processes infix arithmetic expressions with correct operator precedence and parentheses support. Implementation uses a two-stack approach to evaluate expressions deterministically and report clear errors for malformed input.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="phases" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <h2>Project Phases</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Specify expression grammar and tokenization rules.</li>
      <li>Implement parser/evaluator using operator and operand stacks.</li>
      <li>Create unit tests and a design document covering edge cases.</li>
      <li>Polish error handling and add robust input validation.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section id="analysis" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <h2>Summary of Analysis</h2>
    <p>
      The evaluator reliably handles nested parentheses and precedence; performance is linear in the length of the tokenized expression. Attention to error messages helped make the tool usable for classmates testing custom input.
    </p>
  </section>
    <section id="reflections" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
      <h2>Reflections</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Reflections:</strong>
        <a href={`${base}/documents/reflections/html/${encodeURIComponent('Reflection -  ExpressionEvaluator.html')}`}>HTML</a>
        {' '}|{' '}
        <a href={`${base}/documents/reflections/pdf/${encodeURIComponent('Reflection -  ExpressionEvaluator.pdf')}`} download target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
      </p>
      <p><a href={`${base}/aden-course`} style="color:#0055aa; text-decoration:underline;">← Back to ADEN Course</a></p>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>